Looking at the proof goal, I need to prove that for all φ ψ, if φ ➝ ψ ∈ T.theory and φ ∈ construction_omega T hT, then ψ ∈ construction_omega T hT.

This follows from the definition of `construction_omega` and how the construction works. When φ ∈ construction_omega, we have χ ➝ φ ∈ T.theory (from the base case or the inductive construction). If φ ➝ ψ ∈ T.theory, then by transitivity we should get χ ➝ ψ ∈ T.theory.

Let me trace through the logic:
- If φ ∈ construction_omega, then either χ ➝ φ ∈ T.theory or φ was added because certain conditions held
- If φ ➝ ψ ∈ T.theory and χ ➝ φ ∈ T.theory, then by `mem_trans` we get χ ➝ ψ ∈ T.theory
- Then ψ ∈ construction_omega by `mem_omega_of_mem`

```lean
lemma construction_rel :
  letI U := construction_omega T hT
  (∀ φ ψ, φ ➝ ψ ∈ T.theory → φ ∈ U → ψ ∈ U) := by
  intro φ ψ hφψ hφ;
  rcases of_mem_construction_omega hφ with hχφ | hΓ;
  · exact mem_omega_of_mem (T.mem_trans hχφ hφψ);
  · apply construction_omega_impClosed (φ := φ);
    · apply T.L_subset;
      apply Logic.iff_provable.mp;
      exact hφψ;
    · exact hφ;
